    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Structures or chambers, often underground, that are reinforced against bombing and typically stocked with food and living essentials, intended to be used by civilians or military personnel in case of enemy bomb attack.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000093795/Encyclopedia Britannica Online (2002-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Constructies of kamers, vaak onder de grond, die zijn versterkt om bominslagen te weerstaan en die gewoonlijk zijn voorzien van voedsel en andere eerste levensbehoeften. Bedoeld om te worden gebruikt door burgers of militair personeel tijdens vijandelijke bombardementen. </Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>強化防彈的構造體或房間，通常在地面下，一般貯存有糧食與維生必需品，一旦敵方以炸彈攻擊時，供民眾或軍方人員使用。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
